TreeScan is a java tool to list folders by size within a tree

usage: java -jar TreeScan.jar [path (string)] <[resolution (B|KB|MB|GB)]> <[limit (int)]> <[full (boolean)]

where: 

- path: 			the folder to scan for
- resolution: 		the dimension of size for items being shown
- limit: 			threshold for items being shown in resolution-units
- full:				if true also '.'-folder will be scanned

